1. *Robijaš* se vraća u zatvor. (The *convict* is returning to prison.)
2. U gradu postoji *robna kuća* u kojoj možeš kupiti sve što ti treba. (There is a *department store* in the city where you can buy everything you need.)
3. Prošle godine sam bila *rob oluje* koja je uništila moju kuću. (Last year, I was a *victim of the storm* that destroyed my house.)
4. Naša zemlja je nekada bila *pod turskim ropstvom*. (Our country was once *under Ottoman rule*.)
5. *Robovlasništvo* je bilo uobičajeno u prošlosti, ali je sada zabranjeno. ( *Slavery* was common in the past, but now it is banned.)
6. *Robovi* su se borili za svoju slobodu i ljudska prava. (*Slaves* fought for their freedom and human rights.)
7. Mnogi ljudi su *robovi* svog posla i ne vole ga, ali ga rade iz nužde. (Many people are *slaves* to their job and don't like it, but they do it out of necessity.)
8. Proizvodnja *roba* se povećala u posljednjih nekoliko godina. (The production of *goods* has increased in the last few years.)
9. *Roblje* je bilo prisiljeno raditi u rudnicima zlata. (*Forced labor* was made to work in gold mines.)
10. On je *rob svojih navika* i ne može promijeniti svoj način života. (He is a *slave to his habits* and cannot change his lifestyle.)